originalSql:
SELECT 
    n.n_name,
    SUM(l.l_extendedprice * (1 - l.l_discount)) AS revenue
FROM 
    part p
JOIN 
    lineitem l ON p.p_partkey = l.l_partkey
JOIN 
    partsupp ps ON p.p_partkey = ps.ps_partkey
JOIN 
    supplier s ON ps.ps_suppkey = s.s_suppkey
JOIN 
    nation n ON s.s_nationkey = n.n_nationkey
WHERE 
    l.l_shipdate >= DATE '1995-01-01' 
    AND l.l_shipdate < DATE '1995-12-31'
GROUP BY 
    n.n_name
ORDER BY 
    revenue DESC

SELECT COALESCE("nation"."n_name", "nation"."n_name") AS "N_NAME", SUM("t"."l_extendedprice" * (1 - "t"."l_discount")) AS "REVENUE"
FROM "nation"
INNER JOIN "supplier" ON "nation"."n_nationkey" = "supplier"."s_nationkey"
INNER JOIN ((SELECT *
FROM "lineitem"
WHERE "l_shipdate" >= DATE '1995-01-01' AND "l_shipdate" < DATE '1995-12-31') AS "t" INNER JOIN ("part" INNER JOIN "partsupp" ON "part"."p_partkey" = "partsupp"."ps_partkey") ON "t"."l_partkey" = "part"."p_partkey") ON "supplier"."s_suppkey" = "partsupp"."ps_suppkey"
GROUP BY "nation"."n_name"

SELECT COALESCE("N_NAME", "N_NAME") AS "N_NAME", "REVENUE"
FROM "s1"
ORDER BY "REVENUE" DESC NULLS FIRST
